  <TITLE>Each catalog page of admin area should have a hint with a hyperlink to the appropriate page of our documentation</TITLE>
  <DESCRIPTION>Let's implement it only for &quot;catalog&quot; (list) pages. So for example, we have the &quot;product list&quot;, &quot; add product&quot; and &quot;edit product&quot; pages. But we'll add the hyperlink to the &quot;product list&quot; page only. So it'll reference to https://docs.nopcommerce.com/running-your-store/catalog/products/index.html. It should have some UI friendly tooltip. For example, &quot;Learn more about products&quot; (and the &quot;products&quot; points to the documentation portal) And the category list page will have a hyperlink to https://docs.nopcommerce.com/running-your-store/catalog/categories.html ...etc</DESCRIPTION>
